programme.title: Birthright
programme.desc: Cory evicted from his rental, moves back with his pregnant wife, Jasmine. Focusing on his parents wealth, he decides to achieve success through unimaginable actions.

programme.title: The Wailing
programme.desc: A group of young people inadvertently resurrects a seemingly invisible evil.

programme.title: Night Shift
programme.desc: The ghost of a nurse known as La Planchada roams the dim corridors of a hospital. Rebeca, a new nurse on probation, must face the mysterious and feared entity while proving her worth to her superiors.

programme.title: Nocturnal Animals
programme.desc: A writer (Jake Gyllenhaal) asks his ex-wife (Amy Adams) to read a manuscript of his new novel, a troubling story about a family man whose life takes a dark turn.

programme.title: Frankenstein
programme.desc: A reporter investigating the Frankenstein legend suspects that the novel is really the true story of a group of 1800s alchemists who are still alive.

programme.title: The Wolf Man
programme.desc: Bitten by a werewolf, an aristocrat (Lon Chaney) grows fangs, fur and a muzzle, then begs his father (Claude Rains) for help.

programme.title: Reagan
programme.desc: From the glitter of Hollywood to the world stage, Ronald Reagan overcomes the odds to become the 40th president of the United States.

programme.title: Mountainhead
programme.desc: Four friends reunite during worldwide economic turmoil.

programme.title: Piece by Piece
programme.desc: Lego bricks tell the life story of singer-songwriter and record producer Pharrell Williams, from his childhood in Virginia to his success in the music and fashion industry.

programme.title: The Alto Knights
programme.desc: In the 1950s, New York crime bosses Frank Costello and Vito Genovese vie for control of the streets. Once the best of friends, petty jealousies and a series of betrayals place them on a deadly collision course that reshapes organized crime forever.

programme.title: Marnie
programme.desc: A man struggles to break the thieving habits of his kleptomaniac wife and restore harmony to their marriage.

programme.title: The Birds
programme.desc: A San Francisco playgirl (Tippi Hedren) follows a bachelor (Rod Taylor) to Bodega Bay where, for no apparent reason, flocks of birds begin killing the populace.

programme.title: Vertigo
programme.desc: A student feels that he has become detached from reality.

programme.title: Psycho
programme.desc: A woman (Anne Heche) steals cash at work, hits the road and stays at a desolate motel run by mad, mother-fixated Norman Bates (Vince Vaughn).

programme.title: Rear Window
programme.desc: A paralyzed architect believes he has witnessed a murder in this remake of Alfred Hitchcocks 1954 classic.

programme.title: The Delinquents
programme.desc: Bank employee Morn steals enough money to never work again. His colleague hides the cash when Morn confesses and serves time. Soon under investigative pressure, accomplice Romn meets a woman who transforms him forever.

programme.title: As Good as It Gets
programme.desc: A New York City waitress (Helen Hunt), a gay painter (Greg Kinnear) and a dog help a misanthropic author (Jack Nicholson) reach a self-awakening.

programme.title: Room
programme.desc: Held captive for years in an enclosed space, a woman and her young son finally gain their freedom, allowing the boy to experience the outside world for the first time.

programme.title: The King Tide
programme.desc: After a child with mysterious powers washes ashore their idyllic island village, the once peaceful community devolves into civil war, torn over the belief that the child is the next savior.

programme.title: The Wolfman
programme.desc: A nobleman (Anthony Hopkins) contends with an ancient curse, scouring his childhood homeland for his missing brother, while a bloodthirsty beast prowls the moors.

programme.title: Dont Worry Darling
programme.desc: Alice and Jack live in Victory, an experimental company town that houses the men who work on a top-secret project. However, when cracks in her seemingly idyllic life begin to appear, Alice suspects something sinister is lurking below the surface.

programme.title: Ex Machina
programme.desc: A young programmer (Domhnall Gleeson) at an Internet company is chosen to evaluate the capabilities and consciousness of a beautiful and sophisticated robot (Alicia Vikander).

programme.title: Priscilla
programme.desc: When teenage Priscilla Beaulieu meets Elvis Presley at a party, the man who is already a meteoric rock n roll superstar becomes someone entirely unexpected in private moments: a thrilling crush, an ally in loneliness, a vulnerable best friend.

programme.title: Anora
programme.desc: Anora, a young woman from Brooklyn, gets her chance at a Cinderella story when she meets and marries the son of an oligarch. Once the news reaches Russia, her fairytale is threatened as the parents set out for New York to get the marriage annulled.
